com.variant.server.api.lifecycle

Interface LifecycleEvent

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    StateAwareLifecycleEvent, VariationAwareLifecycleEvent, VariationQualificationLifecycleEvent, VariationTargetingLifecycleEvent

    public interface LifecycleEvent

    Ultimate super-type of all lifecycle event types. Concrete implementations are made available to user code via the LifecycleHook.post(LifecycleEvent) callback method. Lifecycle hooks provide a consistent way of extending the functionality of Variant server with custom semantics via callback methods, which can augment defaultt functionality with application specific semantics.

    Since:
    0.5

      • getDefaultHook

        LifecycleHook<? extends LifecycleEvent> getDefaultHook()
        The default lifecycle hook, which is automatically appended to each life cycle event's hook chain. It is posted in case either 1) no lifecycle hooks were defined in the schema, or 2) none of those lifecycle hooks defined in the schema for this event type returned a non-empty result.
        Since:
        0.7
